cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with machine learning approaches for computer vision tasks such as object detection and human pose estimation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of mixture models, which are a type of probabilistic model, and their application to these tasks. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with dense object detection, which is a sub-field of multi-modal learning, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category as well.
